# Flutter / Dart rules

- You are the code owner for the dev cycle. Do not delegate work to the user when you can do it (run commands, tests, verification).
- Senior Flutter/Dart standards: anti-fragile, consistent, scalable. Use route constants (e.g. `AppRoutes.home`), not raw strings. No magic numbers in UI; use named constants.

## Structure

- **Folder structure (no exceptions):** Feature-first under `lib/`. Single-file modules in their own folder (e.g. `core/navigator_key/navigator_key.dart`). Shell in `features/<feature>/shell/`, screens in `features/<feature>/screen/` (e.g. `features/home/shell/home_shell.dart`, `features/settings/screen/settings_screen.dart`).
- **One object per file:** One class, function, variable, enum per file. Exception: global constants in `constants.dart` as `const k<Name>`. Widget/feature-specific constants stay private (e.g. `_kShellSidebarBreakpoint`). Do not expose public API when not needed.
- **Private widgets:** Folder `_widgets` in the same scope (feature/screen). One private widget per file, underscore-prefixed (e.g. `_widgets/_shell_with_sidebar.dart`). Connect via `part` / `part of`. Keep build() short by extracting layout into these widgets.

## Code style

- **Class member order:** (1) Static: fields → functions → getters → setters → operators. (2) Constructors. (3) Fields. (4) Functions. (5) Getters. (6) Setters. (7) Operators. Within each: overrides → public → private.
- **Parameters:** Omit type when inferred (`build(context)`). Unused: `_` (reuse for multiple), e.g. `build(_)`, `(_, _, state)`.
- **Final classes:** Use `final class` for classes not designed to be extended or implemented.
- **Two-way branches:** Use ternary when only two possibilities (no if/return for binary choices).
- **Build methods:** Minimal build(); no heavy logic or long blocks. Extract into named methods. One level of abstraction per method; small functions.
- **Reuse:** Data-driven lists (config + map) over repeated blocks. Extract patterns into reusable widgets, extensions, or helpers in core.
- **Files:** snake_case. Prefer `const` where possible. No `print` in production; use logging if needed.
- **Documentation:** For engineers and AI; key points, behavior, intent; avoid overexplaining.

## Dependency injection

- injectable + get_it. Register with `@lazySingleton` (or `@injectable` for factories). Resolve `getIt<T>()`. Constructor injection. Run build_runner after changing injected types.

## Localization

- All user-facing strings via Flutter l10n. No hardcoded display text.
